# Ghidra / AgentDecompile

## Prefer these tools

| Need | Tool |
|------|------|
| Discovery | `search-everything` (batch `queries`) |
| One function | `get-function` |
| Xrefs | `get-references` |
| Call graph | `get-call-graph` |
| Types | `manage-structures`, `apply-data-type` |
| Cross-build | `match-function`, `migrate-metadata` |

## Discipline

- Pass `program_path` when multiple binaries are open — **JSON string** form: `"/TSL/k2_xbox_default.xbe"`
- Checkout before mutating shared Ghidra projects
- Prefer `get-function` (asm + graph); if decompiler fails, **do not block** — export disassembly for `settings.yaml` `asm`
- On shared Odyssey server, PC `.exe` / Linux `.elf` may fail decompiler launch; Xbox `.xbe` disassembly still works
- Rename (`manage-function`) and comment (`manage-comments`) as you learn

## Handoff to decomp

Export asm, signatures, and types into `prompts/<fn>/` (or folder named in `mizuchi.yaml` `promptsDir`) via `decomp-prompt-architect`.

Read skill: `ghidra-re-workflow`.
